- **Latest Version of Spring Boot**: 3.x
- **Key Config Options**:
  - `spring.kafka.bootstrap-servers`: Kafka broker addresses.
  - `spring.cloud.stream.bindings.input.destination`: Input topic name.
  - `spring.cloud.stream.bindings.output.destination`: Output topic name.
- **CLI Commands**:
  - To create a new Spring Boot project with Kafka Streams: `mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example -DartifactId=kafka-streams-demo -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false`
  - To run the application: `./mvnw spring-boot:run`
- **Example Code Snippet**:
  ```java
  @SpringBootApplication
  public class KafkaStreamsDemoApplication {
      public static void main(String[] args) {
          SpringApplication.run(KafkaStreamsDemoApplication.class, args);
      }
  }

  @StreamListener(Sink.INPUT)
  @SendTo(Sink.OUTPUT)
  public String process(String message) {
      return "Processed: " + message;
  }
  ```
- **Dependencies**:
  - Add `spring-cloud-stream` and `spring-kafka-streams` to your `pom.xml`.
- **Real-life Examples**:
  - Real-time data processing.
  - Event sourcing.
  - Stream analytics.
